metadata.description:
PSSSSD

A conceptual piece created in 2022 written and produced by myself.

The song has become a refreshing reminder to myself that we really have no limits on creative freedom. There is nothing stopping us from creating and defining music in our own terms. Being just over a minute long PSSSSD features one verse, two chorus's, and an experimental beat breakdown.

Thank you to every person that has supported, collected, or listened to my music. 

This is PSSSSD.

lyrics.text:
I’ve been feeling broken
Going through the motions
I’m obsessed, but I’m losing time

But part of me feels like I’ve finally woken
I’m possessed but I’m feeling fine

Sick of time
Taking all my wires
Walking blind
Putting out these fires
Like who am I?
Just an empty fighter
To stay alive
I’m preaching to the choirs

A moment of truth
Maybe it’s cutting me loose
Fire away
Step in my shoes
We’re trained to salute
The hierarchy

I feel like I could be changing
Wanna rewire my mainframe
Stepping away from the same things

I’ve been feeling broken
Going through the motions
I’m obsessed, but I’m losing time

But part of me feels like I’ve finally woken
I’m possessed but I’m feeling fine
